  • skew =
  • kurto = 
skew.and.kurto <- function(x){

  num1 <- mean((x-mean(x))^3)
  denom1 <- (mean((x-mean(x))^2))^1.5
  num2 <- mean((x-mean(x))^4)
  denom2 <- (mean((x-mean(x))^2))^2
  skew <- num1/denom1
  kurto <- num2/denom2 - 3
  
  return(c(skew, kurto))
}

z <- rnorm(1000)
sk <- skew.and.kurto(z)
sk
## [1] 0.049277331 0.009081862

nreps <- 1000

ll <- numeric(nreps)
ul <- numeric(nreps)

n <- 100
mu <- 500
sigma <- 100

for (i in 1:nreps) {
  set.seed(i)
  x <- rnorm(n, mu, sigma)
  ll[i] <- mean(x) - qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(sigma^2/n)
  ul[i] <- mean(x) + qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(sigma^2/n)
}

which(ll >= 500)
